column1: # Model: Name of the sea ice forecast model

# Ensemble member: Name of the ensemble member. Only relevant for IceNet models - for SEAS5 and the linear trend model this is 'NA'. IceNet's temperature-scaled ensemble mean is labelled 'ensemble_tempscaled'. The non-temperature-scaled ensemble mean is labelled 'ensemble'
# Leadtime: Lead time of the forecast (number of months)
# Forecast date: Monthly-average target forecast date (day set to 01 by default)
# Binary accuracy: Percentage of grid cells with the correct binary prediction for SIC > 15% from the model
column2: computed within a maximum sea ice climatology mask (%)

column1: # SIE error: Sea ice extent (area covered by grid cells with SIC > 15%) error between model and OSI-SAF ground truth (km2)
